len于1485年出生在英国英格兰素福爾可时，他的父亲John Allen46岁，母亲Agnes J Norton36岁。他与Eleanor R Burton结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1552年在他的家乡享年67岁。"},"hr":{"1485–1552":"1485.–1552.","1480–1500":"1480–1500.","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485.","1449–1485":"1449–1485.","1469":"1469.","1500":"1500.","1552":"1552.","1485":"1485.","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"oko 1505.","1480":"1480","about 1485":"oko 1485.","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485","1449–1485":"1449–1485","1469":"1469","1500":"1500","1552":"1552","1485":"1485","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"okolo 1505","1480":"1480","about 1485":"okolo 1485","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Anglie","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, Anglie","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485","1449–1485":"1449–1485","1469":"1469","1500":"1500","1552":"1552","1485":"1485","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"omkring 1505","1480":"1480","about 1485":"omkring 1485","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485","1449–1485":"1449–1485","1469":"1469","1500":"1500","1552":"1552","1485":"1485","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"circa 1505","1480":"1480","about 1485":"circa 1485","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485","1449–1485":"1449–1485","1469":"1469","1500":"1500","1552":"1552","1485":"1485","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"about 1505","1480":"1480","about 1485":"about 1485","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Allen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: from the Middle English, Old French personal name <i>Alain</i>, <i>Alein</i> (Old Breton <i>Alan</i>), from a Celtic personal name of great antiquity and obscurity. In England the personal name is now usually spelled <i>Alan</i>, the surname <i>Allen</i>; in Scotland the surname is more often <i>Allan</i>. From 1139 it was common in Scotland, where the surname also derives from Gaelic <i>Ailéne</i>, <i>Ailín</i>, from <i>ail</i> ‘rock’. The present-day frequency of the surname Allen in England and Ireland is partly accounted for by the popularity of the personal name among Breton followers of William the Conqueror, by whom it was imported first to Britain and then to Ireland. Saint Alan(us) was a 5th-century bishop of Quimper, who was a cult figure in medieval Brittany. Another Saint Al(l)an was a Cornish or Breton saint of the 6th century, to whom a church in Cornwall is dedicated.","English: occasionally perhaps from the rare Middle English femaje personal name <i>Aline</i> (Old French <i>Adaline</i>, <i>Aaline</i>), a pet form of ancient Germanic names in <i>Adal-</i>, especially <i>Adalheidis</i> (see   Allis  ).","French: variant of   Allain  , a cognate of 1 above, and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."],"variants":[{"name":"Allenby","meanings":["English: habitational name from Allonby (Cumberland). The placename is a post-Conquest compound of the French (Breton) personal name <i>Alein</i> (see   Allen  ) + Old Norse <i>bȳ</i> ‘village’, or the same word borrowed into Middle English."]},{"name":"Allin","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Allen  .","Swedish: variant of   Ahlin  ."]},{"name":"Alano","meanings":["Italian (mainly Campania) and Hispanic (mainly Philippines): from the personal name <i>Alano</i> (see   Allen  )."]},{"name":"Alan","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Allen  . This is the usual form of the personal name in England and Scotland."]},{"name":"Allan","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: variant of   Allen  . This is the more common form of the name in Scotland and northern England. See also   McAllen  .","History: An early bearer of this surname in North America was William Allan, a British soldier who took his family to the newly founded city of Halifax, NS, Canada, in 1749. His son John (1746–1805) was a Revolutionary soldier who eventually (1783) founded the settlement of Allan's Island, Passamaquoddy Bay, ME."]},{"name":"Allain","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jean-Paul, Adelard, Alban, Albenie, Alphonse, Andree, Cyrille, Donat, Emile, Euclide, Francois.","Breton and French: from the Old Breton personal name <i>Alan</i> (Old French <i>Alain</i>); see   Allen  . In France the personal name is spelled <i>Alain</i>, and this is also a less common variant of the surname (see   Alain  ).","English: variant of   Allen  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Alen","meanings":["English: variant of   Allen  .","Galician (<b>Alén</b>): habitational name from one of the many places called Alén in Galicia (Spain), from Galician <i>alén</i> ‘beyond’.","Flemish and Dutch: patronymic from   Ale  ."]},{"name":"Allis","meanings":["English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Alis</i>, <i>Alice</i> (Old French <i>Adeliz</i>, <i>Ahelis</i>, <i>Aalis</i>, <i>Aliz</i>). <i>Alice</i>, together with its pet form <i>Alison</i>, was one of the most popular names in both England and Scotland from the 13th century until the end of the medieval period. The personal name is of ancient Germanic origin, brought to England from France by the Normans; it is a shortened form of ancient Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>, which is composed of the elements <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>haid</i> ‘‘rank, worth’’."]},{"name":"Alleyne","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Camille, Chantal, Julien, Marcell.","English: variant of   Allen  . This is an old-fashioned spelling, already established as a surname in England in Tudor times. Today this surname is found mainly in the West Indies, especially Barbados."]},{"name":"Alling","meanings":["English: either a variant of   Allen  , or a variant of   Halling   with loss of initial <i>H-</i>.","German: habitational name from either of two places called Alling, one in Bavaria and one in Austria.","Danish: habitational name from any of several places called Alling. The placename may be a derivative of <i>al</i> ‘alder’."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph Allen was born in 1485, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Allen, was 46 and his mother, Agnes J Norton, was 36. He married Eleanor R Burton. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1552, in his hometown, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"1440–1485","1449–1485":"1449–1485","1469":"1469","1500":"1500","1552":"1552","1485":"1485","1584":"1584","1440":"1440","Abt 1500":"umbes 1505","1480":"1480","about 1485":"umbes 1485","1505":"1505","1449":"1449","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Cranfield, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cranfield, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Brokenhaugh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, England","Brokenhaugh, Warden, Northumberland, England":"Warden, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–1552":"1485–1552","1480–1500":"1480–1500","1505–1584":"1505–1584","1440–1485":"